The bodies of a woman and her baby were found floating in a dam in Allanridge, in the Free State, police said on Tuesday. Police spokesperson Capt Stephen Thakeng said the bodies of the 29-year-old woman and her 7-month baby boy were found by a passerby on Sunday. Police were immediately called to the scene. Thakeng said it was later found that the woman had been raped. A double murder case had been opened.Â No arrests have been made.